---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBand from '@/components/CtaBand.astro';
import { business } from '@/config/business';
---

<Base
  title="Solar for Your NJ Home | Paragon Exteriors + Ray Energy"
  description="Thinking solar at the Jersey Shore? Paragon Exteriors preps your roof for panels and partners with Ray Energy for the solar install — roof and solar coordinated, done once, done right."
>
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <p class="font-display text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-300">Solar-ready roofing</p>
      <h1 class="h-display mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Solar starts with the roof under it</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg text-white/85">
        Panels last 25+ years — they should never go on a roof that won't. We make sure your roof is solar-ready, and
        our solar partner handles the panels.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6">
    <div class="prose-paragon">
      <p>
        Joe spent over 15 years in solar roofing before co-founding Paragon Exteriors, so we've seen the expensive
        mistake up close: panels installed on a 15-year-old roof, then removed and re-installed (at $2,000–$5,000
        extra) when the roof needs replacing five years later.
      </p>
      <h2>The right order of operations</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Roof assessment first.</strong> If your roof has less than 15 years of life left, replace it before panels go up — <a href="/roof-replacement/">we handle that</a>, usually in a day.</li>
        <li><strong>Solar design & install.</strong> Our trusted partner <a href="https://www.rayenergysolarfree.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Ray Energy</a> handles panel design, permits, incentives, and installation.</li>
        <li><strong>One coordinated project.</strong> Roof and solar scheduled back-to-back — no double mobilization, no finger-pointing between contractors, flashing and penetrations done by roofers who warranty their work.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Ready to explore solar, or not sure your roof qualifies? <a href="/contact/">Get a free roof assessment</a> or
        call {business.phone} — we'll give you a straight answer before anyone sells you panels.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <CtaBand heading="Get your roof solar-ready" sub="Free assessment. Honest answer on whether your roof is up for it." />
</Base>
